{"title_page": "Orlando Bloom", "text_new": "{{short description|English actor}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Orlando Bloom\n| image              = Orlando Bloom Cannes 2013.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Bloom at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]]\n| birth_name         = Orlando Jonathan Blanchard Bloom\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1977|1|13}}\n| birth_place        = [[Canterbury]], [[Kent]], England\n| residence          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[London]], England\n* [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\n}}\n| education          = [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor| UNICEF ambassador}}\n| years_active       = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Miranda Kerr]]|2010|2013|end=divorced}}\n| partner            = [[Katy Perry]] (2016\u2013present; engaged)\n| children           = 1\n\n}}\n\n'''Orlando Jonathan Blanchard Copeland Bloom'''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bloom |first1=Orlando |title=Orlando Bloom on Katy Perry, never saying 'no' and being open |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oVAWc85LfJM |website=Youtube |publisher=The Sunday Times Style |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> (born 13 January 1977)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elflady.com/legolasgreenleaf/print/05mar/images/familyhistory_05mar_01.jpg|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120220054058/http://elflady.com/legolasgreenleaf/print/05mar/images/familyhistory_05mar_01.jpg|url-status=dead|archive-date=20 February 2012|title=Wayback Machine|author=|date=20 February 2012}}</ref> is an English actor. He made his breakthrough as the character [[Legolas]] in [[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' film series]], a role he reprised in [[The Hobbit (film series)|''The Hobbit'' film series]]. He gained further acclaim by appearing in epic fantasy, historical, and adventure films, most notably as [[Will Turner]] in the [[Pirates of the Caribbean (film series)|''Pirates of the Caribbean'' film series]].\n\nBloom subsequently established himself as a [[leading man]] in Hollywood films, with roles such as [[Paris (mythology)|Paris]] in ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]'' (2004) and [[Balian de Ibelin]] in ''[[Kingdom of Heaven (film)|Kingdom of Heaven]]'' (2005). He currently stars in the [[Amazon Prime Video]] series ''[[Carnival Row]]'' (2019\u2013present).\n\nHe made his professional stage debut in [[West End theatre|West End]]'s ''[[In Celebration (play)|In Celebration]]'' at the [[Duke of York's Theatre]] in London in 2007 and starred in a [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] adaption of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' in 2013. In 2009, Bloom was named a [[UNICEF]] Goodwill Ambassador. In 2015 he received the [[BAFTA]] [[Britannia Awards|Britannia Humanitarian Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/08/britannia-awards-meryl-streep-sam-mendes-james-corden-1201502512/|title=Meryl Streep, Sam Mendes & James Corden To Be Lauded At 2015 Britannia Awards|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=20 August 2015|access-date=13 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215173503/https://deadline.com/2015/08/britannia-awards-meryl-streep-sam-mendes-james-corden-1201502512/|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nBloom was born on 13 January 1977 in [[Canterbury]], [[Kent]], and was named after the 16th-century English composer [[Orlando Gibbons]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Orlando Bloom|url=http://www.people.com/people/orlando_bloom/0,,,00.html|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate=3 August 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120701201944/http://www.people.com/people/orlando_bloom/0,,,00.html|archivedate=1 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Orlando Bloom|url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/profiles/orlando-bloom/|work=Hello magazine|accessdate=3 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120627225446/http://www.hellomagazine.com/profiles/orlando-bloom/|archive-date=27 June 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> He has an older sister, Samantha Bloom.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.courier.co.uk/Orlando-Bloom-s-big-sister-stage-Canterbury/story-12019555-detail/story.html|title=Orlando Bloom's big sister on stage at Canterbury|author=<!-- Staff -->|work=[[Kent and Sussex Courier]]|date=22 January 2009|accessdate=1 June 2016}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOrlando initially believed that his biological father was his mother's husband (his stepfather), the [[Jew]]ish South African-born anti-[[Apartheid]] novelist [[Harry Bloom|Harry Saul Bloom]] (1913\u20131981), who died when Bloom was four years old. However, when he was thirteen, Bloom's mother revealed to him that his biological father was actually Colin Stone, his mother's partner and family friend.<ref name=\"ancestry2\" /><ref>[http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/movies/orlandos-sister-denies-feud/story-e6frfmvr-1111113842281 \"Orlando Bloom's sister denies feud\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160428093646/http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/movies/orlandos-sister-denies-feud/story-e6frfmvr-1111113842281 |date=28 April 2016 }}, The Daily Telegraph, 28 June 2007</ref><ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/> Stone, the principal of the Concorde International language school,<ref name=\"Colinstone\">{{cite web|last=Stone|first=Colin|authorlink=|title=About Us|publisher=Concorde International|date=|url=http://www.concorde-int.com/about.htm|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070402172800/http://www.concorde-int.com/about.htm|archive-date=2 April 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> became Orlando Bloom's legal guardian after Harry Bloom's death.<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/>\n\nBloom's mother, Sonia Constance Josephine (''n\u00e9e'' Copeland), was born in [[Kolkata]], [[India]], the daughter of Francis John Copeland, a physician and surgeon, and Betty Constance Josephine (''n\u00e9e'' Walker). Through her, Bloom is a cousin of photographer [[Sebastian Copeland]].<ref name=\"Copeland2008\">{{cite book|author=Sebastian Copeland|title=Antarctica: A Call to Action|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YuwKLAAACAAJ|date=18 November 2008|publisher=Earth Aware Editions|isbn=978-1-60109-027-0 |section=Foreword}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://environment.uk.msn.com/photos/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=8306308&imageindex=4 |title=Sebastian Copeland (known as Baste)&nbsp;\u2013 MSN Environment UK |publisher=Environment.uk.msn.com |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Bloom's mother's family lived in [[Tasmania]] (Australia), Japan, and India, and were of English descent, some of them having originally come from [[Kent]].<ref name=\"ancestry2\">{{cite news|last=Barratt|first=Nick|title=Family Detective|pages=|publisher=Telegraph|date=11 November 2006|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/exclusions/familyhistory/nosplit/fd4.xml|accessdate=26 May 2007|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080106214346/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=%2Fnews%2Fexclusions%2Ffamilyhistory%2Fnosplit%2Ffd4.xml|archive-date=6 January 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom was brought up in the [[Church of England]].<ref>[http://www.independentfilmquarterly.com/ifq/interviews/orlandobloom.htm Independent Film Quarterly&nbsp;\u2013 IFQ Magazine Interview with Orlando Bloom] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080322012700/http://www.independentfilmquarterly.com/ifq/interviews/orlandobloom.htm |date=22 March 2008 }}</ref> He attended St Peter's Methodist Primary School,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.st-peters-canterbury.kent.sch.uk/p_Where_Are_They_Now.ikml |title=St. Peter's Methodist Primary School, Canterbury |publisher=St-peters-canterbury.kent.sch.uk |date=13 January 1977 |accessdate=5 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407094719/http://www.st-peters-canterbury.kent.sch.uk/p_Where_Are_They_Now.ikml |archivedate=7 April 2014 |df= }}</ref> then the junior school of the [[The King's School Canterbury|King's School]] before proceeding to [[St Edmund's School]] in Canterbury. Bloom was discovered to be [[dyslexic]],<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/><ref name=\"files\">{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Learning Disability|pages=|publisher=J-14|url=http://www.theorlandobloomfiles.com/articles/j1404march.html|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070603094801/http://www.theorlandobloomfiles.com/articles/j1404march.html|archive-date=3 June 2007|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and was encouraged by his mother to take art and drama classes.<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/> After being spurred into action following his school prize submission to panto actor Richard Sieben in 1992, in 1993, he moved to London to follow a two-year [[A Level]] course in Drama, Photography and Sculpture at [[Fine Arts College]], Hampstead. He then joined the [[National Youth Theatre]], spending two seasons there and earning a scholarship to train at the British American Drama Academy.<ref name=\"APStory\"/> Bloom began acting professionally with television roles in episodes of ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' and ''[[Midsomer Murders]]'',<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/> and subsequently made his film debut in ''[[Wilde (film)|Wilde]]'' (1997), opposite [[Stephen Fry]], before entering the [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]] in London, where he studied acting.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biographyworld.net/Orlando-Bloom-Biography.htm|title=Orlando Bloom Biography|website=www.biographyworld.net|access-date=2018-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170714075912/http://biographyworld.net/Orlando-Bloom-Biography.htm|archive-date=14 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Orlando Bloom 3.jpg|thumb|180px|Bloom at the ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest]]'' London premiere, July 2006]]\nBloom's first appearance on the screen was in a small role, as a [[rent boy]], in the 1997 film ''[[Wilde (film)|Wilde]]''. Two days after graduating from Guildhall in 1999,<ref name=\"Bloomsinterview507\">{{cite news|last=Pearce|first=Garth|title=On the move: Orlando Bloom|pages=|work=The Sunday Times |date=27 May 2007|url=http://driving.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/driving/article1839396.ece|accessdate=27 May 2007 | location=London}}</ref> he was cast in his first major role, playing [[Legolas]] in [[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' film trilogy]] (2001\u20132003).<ref name=\"APStory\"/> He had originally auditioned for the part of [[Faramir]], who does not appear until the second movie, but the director, [[Peter Jackson]], cast him as Legolas instead. While shooting a scene, he broke a rib after falling off a horse, but eventually recovered and continued shooting.<ref name=\"wildabout\">{{cite news|last=Nasson|first=Tim|title=Orlando Bloom Interview|pages=|publisher=Wild About Movies|url=http://www.wildaboutmovies.com/interviews/WildAboutMoviesOrlandoBloom_Interview_ElizabethtownMovie.php|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070504173330/http://www.wildaboutmovies.com/interviews/WildAboutMoviesOrlandoBloom_Interview_ElizabethtownMovie.php|archive-date=4 May 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> At the same time, Bloom also played a brief role in [[Ridley Scott]]'s war film ''[[Black Hawk Down (film)|Black Hawk Down]]'' as PFC Todd Blackburn. In 2002, he was chosen as one of the ''[[Teen People]]'' \"25 Hottest Stars Under 25\" and was named ''[[People (magazine)|People]]''{{'s}} hottest Hollywood bachelor in the magazine's 2004 list.<ref name=\"APStory\" /> All members of the cast of the Rings films were nominated for Best Ensemble Acting at the [[Screen Actors Guild|Screen Actors Guild Awards]] for three years in a row, finally winning in 2003 for the third film, ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]]''.  Bloom has also won other awards, including [[European Film Awards]], Hollywood Festival Award, [[Sony Ericsson Empire Awards|Empire Awards]] and [[Teen Choice Award]]s, and has been nominated for many others. Most of Bloom's box office successes have been as part of an [[ensemble cast]].<ref name=\"teenhollywood\">{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Alison|title=Celebrity Interview: Where There's a Will...|publisher=TeenHollywood.com|date=23 May 2007|url=http://www.teenhollywood.com/2007/05/23/celebrity-interview-where-theres-a-will|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055811/http://www.teenhollywood.com/2007/05/23/celebrity-interview-where-theres-a-will|archive-date=23 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom next starred opposite [[Keira Knightley]] and [[Johnny Depp]] in ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl]]'', which was a blockbuster hit during the summer of 2003. After the success of ''Pirates'', Bloom next took to the screen as Paris, the man who effectively started the [[Trojan War]], in the 2004 Spring blockbuster, ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]'' opposite [[Brad Pitt]], [[Eric Bana]] and [[Peter O'Toole]]. He subsequently played the lead roles in Ridley Scott's ''[[Kingdom of Heaven (film)|Kingdom of Heaven]]'' and [[Cameron Crowe]]'s ''[[Elizabethtown (film)|Elizabethtown]]'' (both 2005). In 2006, Bloom starred in sequel ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest]]'' and in the independently made ''[[Haven (film)|Haven]]'', of which he was also executive producer. In the same year he was one of the guest stars in the sitcom ''[[Extras (TV series)|Extras]]'', in which he portrayed an exaggeratedly arrogant, [[narcissistic]] version of himself who had a great loathing for [[Johnny Depp]] (his co-star in ''Pirates of the Caribbean''); Bloom pushed for ''Extras'' to go further by making his part unlikable, and contributed to the gag about him admiring Depp out of sheer jealousy, that Depp was far more talented than he was, not to mention rated higher than him on the 'top hottest' charts.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gordon |first=Scott |url=https://www.avclub.com/content/node/57393/2 |title=Ricky Gervais The A.V. Club |publisher=Avclub.com |date=10 January 2007 |accessdate=19 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218004136/http://www.avclub.com/content/node/57393/2 |archivedate=18 December 2008 |df= }}</ref> Also in 2006, Bloom was the most searched male on [[Google News]].<ref name=\"Pilgersam\">{{cite news|last=Pilger|first=Sam|title=Va-Va Bloom|pages=|publisher=The Sunday Telegraph|date=27 May 2007|url=http://www.news.com.au/sundaytelegraph/story/0,,21792764-5006011,00.html|accessdate=26 May 2007}}</ref> As of May 2007, Bloom has appeared in four of the top 15 highest-grossing films of all time.<ref name=\"Bloomsinterview507\"/>\n[[File:Orlando Bloom 2010.jpg|thumb|170px|left|Bloom at the location filming of ''[[The Three Musketeers (2011 film)|The Three Musketeers]]'' in [[W\u00fcrzburg]], Germany, 14 September 2010]]\nBloom then again portrayed Will Turner, in ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End]]'', released on 24 May 2007. Bloom, who had intended to become a stage actor after graduating from the Guildhall School of Music and Drama, had stated that he would like to leave films for a time and instead appear in stage roles,<ref name=\"APStory\">{{cite news|last=Cohen|first=Sandy|title=Orlando Bloom sails onto new seas|pages=|publisher=Sun Herald|date=24 May 2007|url=http://www.sunherald.com/362/story/61282.html|accessdate=24 May 2007 }}{{dead link|date=August 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> and is \"avidly looking for the right sort of material that [he] can do something with\"<ref name=\"entertainmentwise\">{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Lowri|title=Orlando Bloom To Ditch Film For The Stage?|pages=|publisher=Entertainment Wise|date=19 September 2006|url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news?id=22430|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928011511/http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news?id=22430|archive-date=28 September 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> and go \"back to basics.\"<ref name=\"Bloomstage\">{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Bloom trades his 'Pirates' sword for London stage|pages=|publisher=Khaleej City Times|date=24 May 2007|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/CityHome.asp?xfile=data/citytimes/2007/May/citytimes_May204.xml&section=citytimes&col=|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927231913/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/CityHome.asp?xfile=data%2Fcitytimes%2F2007%2FMay%2Fcitytimes_May204.xml&section=citytimes&col=|archive-date=27 September 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> During the summer of 2007 he appeared in a London revival of ''[[In Celebration (play)|In Celebration]]'', a play by [[David Storey]].<ref name=\"Bloomstage\"/><ref name=\"Bloomstagedate\">{{cite news|last=Lipton|first=Brian Scott|title=Farr, Hilton, et al. to Join Orlando Bloom in London's In Celebration|pages=|publisher=Theater Mania|date=25 May 2007|url=http://www.theatermania.com/content/news.cfm/story/10833|accessdate=25 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070527190828/http://www.theatermania.com/content/news.cfm/story/10833|archive-date=27 May 2007|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His character was one of three brothers returning home for their parents' 40th wedding anniversary.<ref name=\"Bloomsville2\">{{cite news|last=World Entertainment News Network |first= |title=Orlando Bloom To Bare All On Stage |pages= |publisher=Starpulse News Blog |date=24 May 2007 |url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2007/05/24/orlando_bloom_to_bare_all_on_stage |accessdate=24 May 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070526130525/http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2007/05/24/orlando_bloom_to_bare_all_on_stage |archivedate=26 May 2007 |df= }}</ref> On 24 August 2007 he made his first ever TV commercial appearance on late-night Japanese TV, promoting the Uno brand of cosmetics maker Shiseido. A \"one night only\", 2-minute version of the Sci-Fi themed commercial kicked off the product's marketing campaign.<ref name=\"shiseido\">{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Orlando Bloom in First TV Commercial|pages=|publisher=Japan Zone|date=24 August 2007|url=http://www.japan-zone.com/news/2007/08/24/orlando_bloom_in_first_tv_commercial.shtml|accessdate=24 August 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070826013927/http://www.japan-zone.com/news/2007/08/24/orlando_bloom_in_first_tv_commercial.shtml|archive-date=26 August 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2008 he signed on to play a small role in the British film ''[[An Education]]''<ref>{{cite magazine\n | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/film/news/e3i5e7b06bed1aab0197231912ae35284bb\n | title = Molina, Bloom, Hawkins set for 'Education'\n | date = 21 February 2008\n | magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]\n | accessdate =12 March 2008\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080413065847/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/film/news/e3i5e7b06bed1aab0197231912ae35284bb<!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 13 April 2008}}</ref> but dropped out to take the lead in [[Johnnie To]]'s film ''Red Circle''. Also in 2009, he was one of many stars to appear in ''[[New York, I Love You]]'', which contained 12 short films in one. He then appeared in ''[[The Three Musketeers (2011 film)|The Three Musketeers]]'' opposite [[Milla Jovovich]], [[Logan Lerman]], [[Matthew Macfadyen]], [[Ray Stevenson (actor)|Ray Stevenson]], [[Luke Evans (actor)|Luke Evans]], [[Juno Temple]] and [[Christoph Waltz]], released in 2011.\n\nBloom reprised his role as Legolas in parts two and three of ''[[The Hobbit (film series)|The Hobbit]]'', Peter Jackson's three-part prequel to ''The Lord of the Rings'' trilogy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ward|first=Kate|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/05/27/orlando-bloom-joins-hobbit/|title=Orlando Bloom Hobbit|website=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 27, 2011|accessdate=5 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105052133/https://ew.com/article/2011/05/27/orlando-bloom-joins-hobbit/|archive-date=5 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom made his Broadway stage debut as Romeo in ''[[Romeo and Juliet (2013 Broadway play)|Romeo and Juliet]]'' in August 2013 at the [[Richard Rodgers Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite news|title = Orlando Bloom Set To Make Broadway Debut In New Take On \u2018Romeo And Juliet\u2019|date = 7 August 2013|url = http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/08/07/orlando-bloom-set-to-make-broadway-debut-in-new-take-on-romeo-and-juliet/|accessdate = 16 August 2013|publisher = [[WCBS-TV]]|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130814143651/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/08/07/orlando-bloom-set-to-make-broadway-debut-in-new-take-on-romeo-and-juliet/|archive-date = 14 August 2013|url-status = live}}</ref> ''The New York Times'' theatre critic Ben Brantley described Bloom's performance as \"a first-rate Broadway debut\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/20/theater/reviews/orlando-bloom-and-condola-rashad-in-romeo-and-juliet.html|title=Orlando Bloom and Condola Rashad in 'Romeo and Juliet'|first=Ben|last=Brantley|date=2013-10-04|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=28 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420053600/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/20/theater/reviews/orlando-bloom-and-condola-rashad-in-romeo-and-juliet.html|archive-date=20 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> in the title role: \"For once, we have a Romeo who evolves substantively, from a posturing youth in love with love, to a man who discovers the startling revelation of real love, with a last-act descent into bilious, bitter anger that verges on madness.\"\n\nIn October 2011, Bloom stated that he would like to return for a [[Pirates of the Caribbean (film series)|fifth ''Pirates of the Caribbean'' film]]. Bloom did reprise his character, Will Turner, in a supporting role in the fifth film, ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales]]'', which was released in May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/pirates-caribbean-5-orlando-bloom-will-turner/|title='Pirates of the Caribbean 5': Orlando Bloom Confirmed to Return|author=|date=|website=screenrant.com|access-date=17 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917232607/http://screenrant.com/pirates-caribbean-5-orlando-bloom-will-turner/|archive-date=17 September 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom is currently starring in the [[Trafalgar Studios]] production of ''[[Killer Joe (play)|Killer Joe]]'', and in the Amazon Prime TV show ''[[Carnival Row]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nBloom has said that he tries \"not to exclude himself from real life as much as possible.\"<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/> During filming in Morocco for ''[[Kingdom of Heaven (film)|Kingdom of Heaven]]'', Bloom rescued and adopted a dog, Sidi (a black [[Saluki]] mix with a white mark on his chest).<ref name=\"Bloomsdog\">{{cite news|last=Slotek |first=Jim |title=Bloom ready to walk the plank |pages= |publisher=24 Hours |date=24 May 2007 |url=http://vancouver.24hrs.ca/Entertainment/2007/05/23/4200811-sun.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070607215950/http://vancouver.24hrs.ca/Entertainment/2007/05/23/4200811-sun.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=7 June 2007 |accessdate=24 May 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Bk-xgsnuFRQC&pg=PA17&lpg=PA17&dq=During+filming+in+Morocco+for+Kingdom+of+Heaven,+Bloom+rescued+and+adopted+a+dog,+Sidi#v=onepage&q=During%20filming%20in%20Morocco%20for%20Kingdom%20of%20Heaven,%20Bloom%20rescued%20and%20adopted%20a%20dog,%20Sidi&f=false|title=Usefully Useless: Everything you'd Never Learn at School (But May Like to Know)|last=Hanks|first=Mark|date=2012-04-30|publisher=Random House|isbn=9781407074238|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, he became a full member of SGI-UK (the UK branch of [[Soka Gakkai International]]), a lay [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] association affiliated with the teachings of [[Nichiren]].<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Orlando Bloom 'converts to Buddhism'|pages=|publisher=Female First|year=2004|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/celebrity/Orlando+Bloom-1695.html|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716020150/http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/celebrity/Orlando+Bloom-1695.html|archive-date=16 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=[[World Entertainment News Network]]|first=|title=Bloom And Bosworth Build Buddhist Retreat|pages=|publisher=TeenHollywood.com|date=31 August 2006|url=http://www.teenhollywood.com/d.asp?r=131159&c=1055|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928073529/http://www.teenhollywood.com/d.asp?r=131159&c=1055|archive-date=28 September 2007|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom has also been a part of [[Global Green]], an environmental company, since the early 2000s.<ref name=\"teenhollywood\"/> As part of his environmental involvement, he has renovated his London home to use [[Photovoltaic module|solar panels]], incorporate recycled materials, and use energy efficient lightbulbs.<ref name=\"Pilgersam\"/><ref name=\"teenhollywood\"/> Bloom has been approached by [[UNICEF]] to act as an international ambassador.<ref name=\"teenhollywood\"/>\n\nBloom has a [[tattoo]] of the Elvish word \"nine\" on his right wrist, written in fictional [[Tengwar]] Elvish script, a reference to his involvement in ''The Lord of the Rings'' as one of the nine members of the [[Fellowship of the Ring (characters)|Fellowship of the Ring]]. The other actors of \"The Fellowship\" ([[Sean Astin]], [[Sean Bean]], [[Billy Boyd (actor)|Billy Boyd]], [[Ian McKellen]], [[Dominic Monaghan]], [[Viggo Mortensen]], and [[Elijah Wood]]) got the same tattoo with the exception of [[John Rhys-Davies]] whose stunt double got the tattoo instead.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wolf|first1=Buck|title='Lord of the Rings' Stars Get Tattoos|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=101332&page=1|accessdate=20 April 2017|agency=[[ABC News]]|date=11 December 2001|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420234946/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/story?id=101332&page=1|archive-date=20 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Applebaum|first1=Stephen|title=Mortensen's battle scars|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/2544149.stm|accessdate=20 April 2017|publisher=BBC|date=5 December 2002|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040619150324/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/2544149.stm|archive-date=19 June 2004|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"tattoo\">{{cite web| url =http://www.scifi.com/sfw/issue348/interview.html |title = The stars of The Lord of the Rings trilogy reach their journey's end| publisher=SciFi.com| accessdate =31 May 2007 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070306100400/http://www.scifi.com/sfw/issue348/interview.html<!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 6 March 2007}}</ref> Bloom also has a tattoo of a sun on his lower left abdomen, which he got at age 15 just before moving to London.\n\nOn 12 February 2009, Bloom actively participated in the 'Australia Unites' fundraiser to raise support for the victims of the [[Black Saturday bushfires|Australian bushfires on 7 February 2009]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,25043499-5012974,00.html|title= Miranda Kerr and Orlando Bloom chip in for bush fire relief|work= [[Herald Sun]]|date= 12 February 2009|accessdate= 12 February 2009|archive-url= https://archive.today/20120629063306/http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/miranda-leads-fire-aid/story-e6frf96x-1111118828531|archive-date= 29 June 2012|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 October 2009, Bloom was named a [[UNICEF]] Goodwill Ambassador. He has been involved in the organisation since 2007 and has visited schools and villages in [[Nepal]] in support of sanitation and education programmes.<ref name=\"Orlando Bloom named UN ambassador\">{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/8303923.stm |publisher=BBC News | title=Orlando Bloom named UN ambassador | date=12 October 2009 | accessdate=20 May 2010}}</ref> Bloom also visited the city of [[Slovyansk]] in eastern Ukraine in April 2016 to raise awareness of the education crisis facing children during the [[2014 pro-Russian conflict in Ukraine|military conflict with Russia]].<ref name=\"UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador Orlando Bloom visits conflict-hit Ukraine to highlight the importance of education in emergencies\">{{cite news | url=https://www.unicef.org/media/media_91052.html | publisher=UNICEF.org | title=UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador Orlando Bloom visits conflict-hit Ukraine to highlight the importance of education in emergencies | date=4 May 2016 | accessdate=8 September 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927022135/https://www.unicef.org/media/media_91052.html | archive-date=27 September 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBloom has sustained several injuries: he broke his left arm and cracked his skull three times, broke his nose while playing [[rugby union]], broke his right leg skiing in Switzerland, broke his left leg in a motorbike crash, and broke his right wrist while snowboarding.<ref name=\"Bloomsinterview507\"/> He also broke his back when he slipped trying to reach a roof terrace of a friend's house and fell three floors.<ref name=\"back\">{{cite web|url = https://www.gq.com/entertainment/celebrities/200510/orlando-bloom-errol-flynn?currentPage=4|title = The Epic Life of Orlando Bloom|magazine = [[Gentleman's Quarterly]]|accessdate = 30 May 2007|date = 2005-10-06|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120331011921/http://www.gq.com/entertainment/celebrities/200510/orlando-bloom-errol-flynn?currentPage=4|archive-date = 31 March 2012|url-status = live}}</ref> He also broke some ribs while shooting ''The Lord of the Rings''.<ref name=\"hisbowbroke\">{{cite web|url=http://themcavoys.tumblr.com/post/37994939814 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130109130059/http://themcavoys.tumblr.com/post/37994939814 |url-status=dead |archive-date=9 January 2013 |title=His bow totally broke |publisher=[[Tumblr]] |accessdate=15 December 2012 }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 July 2009, four hooded teenagers broke into the [[Hollywood Hills]] home of Orlando Bloom and stole nearly half a million dollars' worth of possessions.  The burglars, dubbed the \"[[Bling Ring]],\" targeted the homes of young celebrities. Most of Bloom's stolen items were retrieved.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-dec-02-la-me-bling-ring2-2009dec02-story.html | title=Alleged 'bling ring' member to stand trial, judge rules | work=[[Los Angeles Times]] | date=December 2, 2009 | accessdate=January 12, 2020 | author=Winton, Richard | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111213424/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2009-dec-02-la-me-bling-ring2-2009dec02-story.html | archive-date=11 January 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Relationships===\nBloom had an \"on-and-off relationship\"<ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/orlando_bloom/biography|title=Orlando Bloom Biography|accessdate=26 September 2010|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100729202913/http://www.people.com/people/orlando_bloom/biography|archive-date=29 July 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> with American actress [[Kate Bosworth]], from 2003 until ending the relationship in September 2006.<ref name=\"CM\">{{cite news|last=|first=|title=LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT FOR BLOOM|pages=|magazine=[[Contact Music]]|date=6 July 2006|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/love%20at%20first%20sight%20for%20bloom_1001772|accessdate=24 May 2007|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66hfWEJAc?url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/love-at-first-sight-for-bloom_1001772|archive-date=5 April 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=All Headline News |first= |title=Orlando Bloom And Kate Bosworth Split |pages= |publisher=Exposay |date=6 September 2006 |url=http://www.exposay.com/orlando-bloom-and-kate-bosworth-split/v/4145/ |accessdate=24 May 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070509072927/http://www.exposay.com/orlando-bloom-and-kate-bosworth-split/v/4145/ |archivedate=9 May 2007 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Orlando Bloom at Venice Festival.jpg|thumb|Bloom at the [[2005 Venice Film Festival]]]]\nIn late 2007, Bloom began dating Australian supermodel [[Miranda Kerr]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-meets-miranda-kerrs-parents/ |title=Orlando Bloom Meets Miranda Kerr's Parents |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=28 April 2010 |accessdate=1 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140118/https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-meets-miranda-kerrs-parents/ |archive-date=1 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> They announced their engagement in June 2010,<ref>{{cite web |first=Eunice |last=Oh |url=https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-and-miranda-kerr-are-engaged/ |title=Orlando Bloom and Miranda Kerr Are Engaged! |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=21 June 2010 |accessdate=1 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140053/https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-and-miranda-kerr-are-engaged/ |archive-date=1 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and were married the following month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-and-miranda-kerr-secretly-marry/|title=Orlando Bloom and Miranda Kerr Secretly Marry!|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=22 July 2010|accessdate=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140139/https://people.com/celebrity/orlando-bloom-and-miranda-kerr-secretly-marry/|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Kerr gave birth to their son on 6 January 2011 in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/parents/miranda-kerr-i-had-a-baby-boy-with-orlando-bloom/ |first=Sarah |last=Michaud |title=Miranda Kerr: I Had a Baby Boy with Orlando Bloom! |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=18 January 2011 |accessdate=1 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140003/https://people.com/parents/miranda-kerr-i-had-a-baby-boy-with-orlando-bloom/ |archive-date=1 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/miranda-kerr-names-flynn-after-late-boyfriend/|title=Miranda Kerr Names Flynn After Late Boyfriend|work=People|first=Alison|last=Schwartz|date=13 July 2011|accessdate=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301140127/https://people.com/parents/miranda-kerr-names-flynn-after-late-boyfriend/|archive-date=1 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 October 2013, Bloom and Kerr announced that they had separated several months earlier, and intended to end their marriage. They were divorced by the end of 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Maresca|first=Rachel|title=Orlando Bloom speaks out on Miranda Kerr separation: 'Life sometimes doesn't work out exactly as we plan'|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/orlando-bloom-speaks-miranda-kerr-separation-article-1.1503669|work=[[NY Daily News]]|accessdate=14 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207114647/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/orlando-bloom-speaks-miranda-kerr-separation-article-1.1503669|archive-date=7 December 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/miranda-kerr-orlando-bloom-split-after-three-years-of-marriage-20132510|first=Allison|last=Takeda|title=Miranda Kerr, Orlando Bloom Split After Three Years of Marriage|work=[[US Weekly]]|date=25 October 2013|accessdate=25 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026165923/http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/miranda-kerr-orlando-bloom-split-after-three-years-of-marriage-20132510|archive-date=26 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBloom began dating American singer [[Katy Perry]] shortly after the [[73rd Golden Globe Awards]] in January 2016;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2016/10/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-instagram-romance-social-media/|magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|date=26 October 2016|accessdate=1 January 2017|title=Katy Perry and Orlando Bloom's Romance: Loud in Public, Muted on Instagram|first=Josh|last=Duboff|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126221443/http://www.vanityfair.com/style/2016/10/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-instagram-romance-social-media|archive-date=26 January 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> however, the couple confirmed in February 2017 that they had split. They resumed their relationship in April 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2018/04/29/katy-perry-and-orlando-bloom-meet-pope-step-out-together-in-rome.html|title=Katy Perry and Orlando Bloom meet the Pope, step out together in Rome|first=Morgan|last=Evans|date=28 April 2018|website=foxnews.com|access-date=30 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429153724/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2018/04/29/katy-perry-and-orlando-bloom-meet-pope-step-out-together-in-rome.html|archive-date=29 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoonewsz.com/entertainment/katy-perry-and-orlando-bloom/|title=A Comprehensive Timeline of Katy Perry and Orlando Bloom's Relationship|website=yahoonewsz.com|date=2019-02-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8403415/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-back-together-pope|title=Katy Perry & Orlando Bloom Met the Pope On Their Roman Holiday|first=Hilary|last=Hughes|date=29 April 2018|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=30 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180520164739/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8403415/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-back-together-pope|archive-date=20 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and they became engaged on 14 February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-get-engaged-on-valentines-day/|title=Katy Perry and Orlando Bloom get engaged on Valentine's Day|work=[[CBS News]]|first=Caitlin|last=O'Kane|date=15 February 2019|accessdate=1 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-engaged|title=Katy Perry and Orlando Bloom Are Engaged! See Her Stunning Ring|work=People|first=Maria|last=Pasquini|first2=Jeff|last2=Nelson|date=15 February 2019|accessdate=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220151724/https://people.com/music/katy-perry-orlando-bloom-engaged/|archive-date=20 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 March 2020, it was revealed through the music video for Perry's single \"[[Never Worn White]]\" that the couple are expecting their first child together, a girl. (If only they got married before the baby!)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/katy-perry-pregnant-baby-orlando-bloom-never-worn-white-music-video-instagram-live-a9376646.html?utm_medium=Social&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583402973|title=Katy Perry pregnant: Singer confirms she is expecting a baby with Orlando Bloom|work=[[The Independent]]|first=Sabrina|last=Barr|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nBloom was named the twelfth most influential person in [[Culture of the United Kingdom|British culture]] in a 2004 poll of cultural experts conducted for the [[BBC]].<ref>{{cite news|title=iPod designer leads culture list|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/3481599.stm|agency=BBC|date=17 November 2016|access-date=17 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810133452/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/3481599.stm|archive-date=10 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Bloom appeared in his home town of Canterbury on 13 July 2010, where he was presented with an honorary degree from the [[University of Kent]] at [[Canterbury Cathedral]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kent.ac.uk/news/stories/honorarydegrees2010/2010 |title=University of Kent Honorary Degrees 2010 |publisher=Kent.ac.uk |date=16 July 2010 |accessdate=19 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203132320/http://www.kent.ac.uk/news/stories/honorarydegrees2010/2010 |archivedate=3 December 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> For contributions to the film industry, Bloom was inducted into the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] on 2 April 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Orlando Bloom's Son Steals The Spotlight At Actor's Walk Of Fame Ceremony|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/04/03/orlando-bloom-son_n_5085093.html?ir=Entertainment|accessdate=5 April 2014|newspaper=Huffingtonpost|date=4 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Orlando Bloom gets Hollywood Walk of Fame star|journal=RT\u00c9.ie|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2014/0403/606364-orlando-bloom-gets-hollywood-walk-of-fame-star/|accessdate=5 April 2014|date=2014-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407015950/http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/2014/0403/606364-orlando-bloom-gets-hollywood-walk-of-fame-star/|archive-date=7 April 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> His [[List of actors with Hollywood Walk of Fame motion picture stars|motion pictures walk of fame star]] is located at 6927 [[Hollywood Boulevard]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walkoffame.com/orlando-bloom |title=Hollywood Walk of Fame - Orlando Bloom |website=walkoffame.com |publisher=Hollywood Chamber of Commerce |accessdate=21 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201045003/http://www.walkoffame.com/orlando-bloom |archive-date=1 December 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"